The best Tucker3 model chosen included five, six and three components for the genotype, gene and internode modes, respectively. This final model explained 49.1% of the total variation in gene expression levels. Of the variance accounted for by the model, 55.1% was due to core element g111\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
